Detailed Description

cvmx_dfa_difctl

To write to DFA_DIFCTL, a device issues an IOBST request directed at the HFA with addr[34:32] = 0x6. To read DFA_DIFCTL, a device issues an IOBLD64 request directed at the HFA with addr[34:32] = 0x6. This register is intended to only be written once (at power-up). Any future write operations could cause the HFA and FPA hardware to become unpredictable.

If DFA_CONFIG[DTECLKDIS] = 1 (i.e. HFA-HTE clocks are disabled) or if FUSE[90] = 'HFA HTE disable' is blown, read/write operations to DFA_DIFCTL do not take effect.
